{% extends "base.html.j2" %}

{% block extra_styles %}
.pro-section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
.pro-section h2 {
  font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink);
  margin: 0 0 0.75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--rule); padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
}
.pro-section p { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.75; }
.pro-section ul { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.8; }
.pro-section table {
  width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.82rem; margin: 1rem 0;
}
.pro-section th {
  background: var(--surface); font-weight: 600; text-align: left;
  padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; border: 1px solid var(--rule);
}
.pro-section td { padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem; border: 1px solid var(--rule); }

.pro-cta-centre {
  text-align: center; margin: 1.5rem 0;
}
.pro-cta-btn {
  display: inline-block; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--hip-blue);
  text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid var(--hip-blue);
  padding: 0.65rem 1.75rem; border-radius: 7px; transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
}
.pro-cta-btn:hover { background: var(--hip-blue); color: #fff; }
.pro-cta-btn-primary {
  display: inline-block; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; text-decoration: none;
  color: #fff; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--hip-blue), var(--hip-blue-deep));
  padding: 0.85rem 2.4rem; border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(14,76,143,0.35); transition: opacity 0.2s, transform 0.15s;
}
.pro-cta-btn-primary:hover { opacity: 0.9; transform: translateY(-1px); color: #fff; }

.ceiling-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}
.ceiling-card {
  background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
  display: block; transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.15s;
  border-top: 4px solid var(--tier-amber);
}
.ceiling-card:hover {
  box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); transform: translateY(-2px);
}
.ceiling-card-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.ceiling-card-title { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.3; }
.ceiling-card-tag {
  font-size: 0.62rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 8px;
  background: #FFF3D6; color: var(--tier-amber-text);
}
.ceiling-card-scores { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: center; }
.ceiling-card-hip {
  font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--tier-amber); line-height: 1;
}
.ceiling-card-hip-label {
  font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #aaa;
}
.ceiling-card-ri {
  font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; margin-left: auto; color: #888;
}
.ceiling-card-date { font-size: 0.68rem; color: #bbb; margin-top: 0.75rem; }
.ceiling-card-category { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #888; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

.ceiling-intro {
  background: #FFF8E6; border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--tier-amber);
  border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--warning-fg);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.no-ceilings { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem; color: #aaa; font-style: italic; }
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}

<h1>For Professionals</h1>
<p>HIP methodology documentation, scoring dimensions, Regenerative Index, and technical resources for researchers, procurement teams, and retail buyers.</p>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>HIP Methodology v1.3</h2>
  <p>The current methodology version is <strong>v1.3</strong>. It defines the scoring model, dimension weights, band thresholds, and the Regenerative Index scale.</p>
  <div class="pro-cta-centre">
    <a class="pro-cta-btn-primary" href="/methodology">Read the Methodology</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>Scoring Dimensions</h2>
  <p>The HIP Score (0–10) is composed of seven weighted dimensions:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Material Scarcity Index</strong> — how abundant or at-risk are the raw materials?</li>
    <li><strong>Supply Chain Risk</strong> — how traceable and resilient is the supply chain?</li>
    <li><strong>Recyclability &amp; Circularity</strong> — can materials be recovered at end of life?</li>
    <li><strong>Repairability</strong> — can the product be repaired and maintained?</li>
    <li><strong>Social &amp; Environmental Impact</strong> — what is the social and environmental footprint?</li>
    <li><strong>Product Longevity</strong> — how long is the product designed to last?</li>
    <li><strong>Regenerative Index</strong> — does the product deplete or restore natural capital?</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>The Regenerative Index</h2>
  <p>Inside the HIP Score sits the Regenerative Index (RI) — a unique scale from −10 to +10 that distinguishes products depleting finite reserves from those actively rebuilding natural capital.</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Band</th><th>Range</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Depleting</td><td>−10 to −6</td><td>Actively drawing down finite material reserves</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Extractive</td><td>−5 to −1</td><td>Net material consumer, limited recovery</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Renewable</td><td>0</td><td>Material equilibrium — input matches recovery</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Restorative</td><td>+1 to +5</td><td>Net material restorer, partial regeneration</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Regenerative</td><td>+6 to +10</td><td>Actively rebuilding natural capital</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>Most consumer products today sit below zero.</p>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>Category Ceilings</h2>
  <div class="ceiling-intro">
    <strong>What is a category ceiling?</strong>
    A ceiling rating shows the best HIP score a product in a given category can achieve when the manufacturer shares full evidence about materials, supply chain, repairs, and end-of-life design.
    Ceilings are benchmarks — not products on sale today. They set the target that verified ratings measure against.
  </div>

  {% if ceilings %}
  <div class="ceiling-grid">
    {% for r in ceilings %}
      {%- if r.ri_descriptor == 'Regenerative' -%}{%- set card_ri_colour = 'var(--ri-regenerative)' -%}
      {%- elif r.ri_descriptor == 'Restorative' -%}{%- set card_ri_colour = 'var(--ri-restorative)' -%}
      {%- elif r.ri_descriptor == 'Renewable'   -%}{%- set card_ri_colour = 'var(--ri-renewable)' -%}
      {%- elif r.ri_descriptor == 'Extractive'  -%}{%- set card_ri_colour = 'var(--ri-extractive)' -%}
      {%- else -%}{%- set card_ri_colour = 'var(--ri-depleting)' -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      <a class="ceiling-card" href="/ratings/{{ r.url_path|default(r.slug) }}">
        <div class="ceiling-card-header">
          <div class="ceiling-card-title">{{ r.title }}</div>
          <span class="ceiling-card-tag">Ceiling</span>
        </div>
        {% if r.category %}
          <div class="ceiling-card-category">{{ r.category }}</div>
        {% endif %}
        <div class="ceiling-card-scores">
          <div>
            <div class="ceiling-card-hip">{{ "%.1f"|format(r.hip_score) }}</div>
            <div class="ceiling-card-hip-label">HIP Score</div>
          </div>
          <div class="ceiling-card-ri" style="color: {{ card_ri_colour }};">
            {% if r.ri_score > 0 %}+{% endif %}{{ "%.1f"|format(r.ri_score) }}<br>
            <span style="font-weight:400; color:#aaa;">{{ r.ri_descriptor }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ceiling-card-date">Assessed {{ r.assessment_date }}</div>
      </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="no-ceilings">No ceiling ratings published yet — check back soon.</div>
  {% endif %}
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>Published Ratings</h2>
  <p>All published ratings — generic category baselines and manufacturer-verified assessments — are publicly available.</p>
  <div class="pro-cta-centre">
    <a class="pro-cta-btn" href="/ratings/">View All Ratings</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>For Retailers and Buyers</h2>
  <p>If you are a retailer, procurement officer, or buying team evaluating products for your range:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Category ratings</strong> show the baseline material resilience of a product type — useful for benchmarking and category-level risk assessment</li>
    <li><strong>Verified ratings</strong> for specific products provide independently assessed, citable evidence for procurement decisions</li>
    <li><strong>The HIP Mark</strong> (Standard, Silver, Gold) provides a simple, consumer-facing signal that a product has met a verified threshold</li>
    <li><strong>Pricing and service terms</strong> are published transparently — see our <a href="/pricing">schedule of fees</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p>For procurement-specific enquiries or bulk assessment requests, <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>Verified Ratings for Manufacturers</h2>
  <p>Manufacturers can commission a Verified Rating to have their specific product assessed against the category baseline using actual product data.</p>
  <div class="pro-cta-centre">
    <a class="pro-cta-btn" href="/verified-ratings">Learn About Verified Ratings</a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="pro-section">
  <h2>Dispute and Correction</h2>
  <p>If you believe a published rating contains an error or is based on outdated information, we have a formal dispute and correction process.</p>
  <div class="pro-cta-centre">
    <a class="pro-cta-btn" href="/dispute">Dispute Process</a>
  </div>
</div>

{% endblock %}
